Carrot cake


Ingredients:

Cake

4 eggs
350 g grated carrots
2.25 dl (1 cup) vedgetable oil
4.5 dl (2 cups) flour
4.5 dl (2 cups) sugar
1 teaspoon baking powder ("bikarbonat" in Swedish)
1 teaspoon baking soda ("bikarbonat" in Swedish)
1 teaspoon salt
1 teaspoon cinnamon

Topping

100 g soft, white cheese (Swedish "Philadelphiaost")
0.5 dl (1/5 cup, 500 g) soft butter
2.25 dl (1 cup) confectioner's sugar
1 teaspoon vanilla sugar


Preparation:

Preheat the oven to 175 C (350 F).  Beat eggs, grated carrots, and oil
until fluffy.  Add the rest and mix well.  Bake for about 60-70
minutes.  Let the cake cool.

Beat cheese, butter, confectioner's sugar, and vanilla sugar until
smooth.  Put it on top of the cake.  Make some fancy pattern with a
fork or something if you feel like it.
